text: Hello! I'm here to help you practice your technical interview skills. Let's start with this problem. What's your initial approach or thought process for solving it?
Okay, I'm looking at the "Insert Interval" problem. I have the list of existing intervals and the new interval to insert. Where should I start?

To begin, can you first think about the different scenarios that might occur when you try to insert a new interval into a sorted list of non-overlapping intervals? Consider how the new interval might relate to the existing ones.
Hmm, okay. The new interval could be completely before all the existing ones, completely after all of them, or it could overlap with some or all of them.
That's a great initial categorization. Can you elaborate on what happens when the new interval overlaps with one or more of the existing intervals? What needs to be considered in those cases?
If it overlaps, I guess I need to merge it with the overlapping intervals. That would involve finding the minimum start and the maximum end of all the merged intervals.
